<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Songa Mobility — Platform Documentation</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --navy: #075155;
    --teal: #1D9E75;
    --teal-light: #E1F5EE;
    --teal-mid: #0F6E56;
    --amber: #EF9F27;
    --text: #1C2B3A;
    --text-muted: #5A6B7A;
    --text-light: #8A9BAA;
    --bg: #F7F9FC;
    --bg-card: #FFFFFF;
    --border: #E2E8EF;
    --sidebar-w: 280px;
    --font-ui: -apple-system,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;
    --font-mono: 'Menlo',monospace;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
  html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
  body{font-family:Georgia,serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-size:16px;line-height:1.75}
  #app{display:flex;min-height:100vh}
  #sidebar{width:var(--sidebar-w);background:var(--navy);position:fixed;top:0;left:0;bottom:0;overflow-y:auto;overflow-x:hidden;display:flex;flex-direction:column;z-index:100}
  #sidebar::-webkit-scrollbar{width:4px}
  #sidebar::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb{background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);border-radius:2px}
  .logo-img{width: 240px;height: 70px;overflow: hidden;}
  .logo-img img{width: 100%;height: 100%;object-fit: scale-down; object-position: center;}
  .logo-img:hover{object-fit: cover;width: 105%;}
  .sidebar-logo{padding:24px 20px 16px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);flex-shrink:0}
  .sidebar-logo .brand{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:4px}
  .sidebar-logo h1{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:17px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;line-height:1.2}
  .sidebar-logo .version{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.28);margin-top:4px}
  #sidebar-search{padding:12px 16px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);flex-shrink:0}
  .search-wrap{position:relative}
  #sidebar-search input{width:100%;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);border-radius:6px;color:#fff;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:13px;padding:7px 10px 7px 28px;outline:none}
  #sidebar-search input::placeholder{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.28)}
  #sidebar-search input:focus{border-color:var(--teal)}
  .search-icon{position:absolute;left:9px;top:50%;transform:translateY(-50%);color:rgba(255,255,255,0.28);font-size:13px;pointer-events:none}
  #nav{padding:8px 0 24px;flex:1}
  .nav-section-label{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.22);padding:16px 20px 6px}
  .nav-item{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;padding:6px 20px;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.58);cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.12s;border-left:2px solid transparent;text-decoration:none;line-height:1.4}
  .nav-item:hover{color:#fff;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.05)}
  .nav-item.active{color:#fff;border-left-color:var(--teal);background:rgba(29,158,117,0.12)}
  .nav-item .num{font-size:10px;font-weight:600;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);min-width:18px;text-align:right;flex-shrink:0}
  .nav-item.active .num{color:var(--teal)}
  #main{margin-left:var(--sidebar-w);flex:1;min-height:100vh}
  #topbar{background:var(--bg-card);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:0 48px;height:54px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:16px;position:sticky;top:0;z-index:50}
  #topbar-search{flex:1;max-width:480px;position:relative}
  #topbar-search input{width:100%;background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:14px;padding:8px 12px 8px 34px;outline:none;color:var(--text);transition:border-color 0.15s,box-shadow 0.15s}
  #topbar-search input:focus{border-color:var(--teal);box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(29,158,117,0.1)}
  #topbar-search input::placeholder{color:var(--text-light)}
  .topbar-search-icon{position:absolute;left:11px;top:50%;transform:translateY(-50%);color:var(--text-light);font-size:14px;pointer-events:none}
  #search-results{position:absolute;top:calc(100% + 6px);left:0;right:0;background:var(--bg-card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);max-height:420px;overflow-y:auto;display:none;z-index:200}
  #search-results.open{display:block}
  .sr-item{padding:12px 16px;cursor:pointer;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);transition:background 0.1s}
  .sr-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .sr-item:hover{background:var(--bg)}
  .sr-item-title{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:2px}
  .sr-item-preview{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;color:var(--text-muted);white-space:nowrap;overflow:hidden;text-overflow:ellipsis}
  .sr-item-chapter{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;color:var(--teal);margin-bottom:3px}
  .sr-empty{padding:24px;text-align:center;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:13px;color:var(--text-muted)}
  .topbar-right{margin-left:auto;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px}
  .topbar-badge{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;background:var(--teal-light);color:var(--teal-mid);padding:3px 8px;border-radius:20px;font-weight:600}
  #content{padding:48px 48px 96px;max-width:820px}
  .chapter-page{display:none}
  .chapter-page.active{display:block}
  .chapter-hero{margin-bottom:40px;padding-bottom:32px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
  .chapter-tag{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--teal);background:var(--teal-light);padding:4px 10px;border-radius:20px;margin-bottom:12px}
  .chapter-hero h1{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:32px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:12px}
  .chapter-hero .lead{font-size:17px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.65;max-width:680px}
  .section-h2{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:20px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);margin:40px 0 12px;padding-top:8px}
  .section-h3{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--teal-mid);margin:28px 0 8px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em}
  .doc-body p{margin-bottom:16px;color:var(--text)}
  .info-box{background:var(--teal-light);border-left:3px solid var(--teal);border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;padding:14px 18px;margin:20px 0;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--teal-mid);font-family:var(--font-ui)}
  .info-box strong{color:var(--teal-mid);font-weight:700}
  .warn-box{background:#FFF8E6;border-left:3px solid var(--amber);border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;padding:14px 18px;margin:20px 0;font-size:14.5px;color:#6B4A00;font-family:var(--font-ui)}
  .doc-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:20px 0;font-size:14px;font-family:var(--font-ui)}
  .doc-table th{background:var(--navy);color:#fff;padding:10px 14px;text-align:left;font-weight:600;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:0.04em}
  .doc-table th:first-child{border-radius:6px 0 0 0}
  .doc-table th:last-child{border-radius:0 6px 0 0}
  .doc-table td{padding:10px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);vertical-align:top;color:var(--text)}
  .doc-table tr:hover td{background:var(--bg)}
  .doc-table td:first-child{font-weight:600;color:var(--teal-mid);white-space:nowrap}
  .badge{display:inline-block;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:20px;letter-spacing:0.03em}
  .badge-green{background:#EAF7F0;color:#0D6B44}
  .badge-amber{background:#FFF3DA;color:#8A5500}
  .badge-red{background:#FFEAEA;color:#991F1F}
  .badge-blue{background:#E6F1FB;color:#185FA5}
  .badge-teal{background:var(--teal-light);color:var(--teal-mid)}
  .badge-gray{background:#F1EFE8;color:#444441}
  .field-list{margin:12px 0 20px}
  .field-item{display:flex;gap:12px;padding:8px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);font-size:14.5px;font-family:var(--font-ui)}
  .field-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .field-name{font-weight:600;color:var(--teal-mid);min-width:160px;flex-shrink:0}
  .field-desc{color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.5}
  code{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13px;background:#F1EEE8;color:#7A3200;padding:1px 5px;border-radius:4px}
  .step-list{counter-reset:step;margin:16px 0 24px}
  .step-item{display:flex;gap:14px;margin-bottom:16px;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:14.5px}
  .step-num{min-width:28px;height:28px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--teal);color:#fff;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px}
  .step-body{color:var(--text);line-height:1.6}
  .step-body strong{color:var(--navy)}
  .home-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:12px;margin:24px 0}
  .home-card{background:var(--bg-card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;padding:18px 20px;cursor:pointer;transition:all 0.15s;text-decoration:none;display:block}
  .home-card:hover{border-color:var(--teal);box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(29,158,117,0.1);transform:translateY(-1px)}
  .home-card-num{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--teal);margin-bottom:6px}
  .home-card-title{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:4px;line-height:1.3}
  .home-card-desc{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;color:var(--text-muted);line-height:1.4}
  .breadcrumb{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;color:var(--text-light);margin-bottom:20px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px}
  .breadcrumb a{color:var(--teal);text-decoration:none;cursor:pointer}
  .breadcrumb a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
  .arch-diagram{background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;padding:24px;margin:20px 0}
  .arch-row{display:flex;gap:12px;margin-bottom:12px;align-items:stretch}
  .arch-box{flex:1;background:var(--bg-card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:14px;font-family:var(--font-ui);text-align:center}
  .arch-box .ab-label{font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:var(--text-light);margin-bottom:4px}
  .arch-box .ab-val{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy)}
  .arch-box .ab-sub{font-size:11px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-top:2px}
  .arch-box.teal{border-color:var(--teal);background:var(--teal-light)}
  .arch-box.teal .ab-val{color:var(--teal-mid)}
  .arch-box.navy{background:var(--navy)}
  .arch-box.navy .ab-label{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.4)}
  .arch-box.navy .ab-val{color:#fff}
  .arch-box.navy .ab-sub{color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5)}
  .flow{display:flex;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:20px 0}
  .flow-step{background:var(--bg-card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:9px 14px;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy)}
  .flow-arrow{font-size:14px;color:var(--text-light)}
  .flow-step.teal{background:var(--teal-light);border-color:var(--teal);color:var(--teal-mid)}
  .pill-wrap{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin:12px 0}
  .pill{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;font-weight:600;padding:5px 12px;border-radius:20px;border:1px solid var(--border);color:var(--text-muted);background:var(--bg-card)}
  ul.doc-ul{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:14.5px;color:var(--text-muted);padding-left:20px;margin:12px 0 20px}
  ul.doc-ul li{margin-bottom:8px}
  ul.doc-ul li strong{color:var(--text)}
  @media(max-width:900px){:root{--sidebar-w:240px}#content{padding:32px 24px 64px}#topbar{padding:0 24px}}

  .doc-screenshot{margin:28px 0;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;background:var(--bg-card);box-shadow:0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06)}
  .doc-screenshot img{width:100%;height:auto;display:block}
  .doc-screenshot figcaption{font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;color:var(--text-muted);padding:10px 14px;border-top:1px solid var(--border);background:var(--bg)}
  .doc-screenshot-wide{}
  .doc-screenshot-tall img{max-height:600px;width:auto;margin:0 auto;display:block}
  .doc-screenshot-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px;margin:28px 0}
  .doc-screenshot-grid .doc-screenshot{margin:0}
  @media(max-width:700px){.doc-screenshot-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}

</style>
</head>
<!-- Début du Body -->
<body>
<div id="app">
<nav id="sidebar">
  <div class="sidebar-logo">
    <div class="logo-img"><img src="img/Songa_logo_white_web.png" onclick="showPage('home',this)"></div>
    <div class="brand">Songa Mobility</div>
    <h1>Platform Docs</h1>
    <div class="version">Web Application · April 2026</div>
  </div>
  <div id="sidebar-search">
    <div class="search-wrap">
      <span class="search-icon">⌕</span>
      <input type="text" id="sidebarSearchInput" placeholder="Quick find…" autocomplete="off"/>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="nav">
    <div class="nav-section-label">Overview</div>
    <a class="nav-item active" data-page="home" onclick="showPage('home',this)"><span class="num">—</span>Home</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch1" onclick="showPage('ch1',this)"><span class="num">01</span>Introduction</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch2" onclick="showPage('ch2',this)"><span class="num">02</span>Platform Architecture</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch3" onclick="showPage('ch3',this)"><span class="num">03</span>Core Entities</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch4" onclick="showPage('ch4',this)"><span class="num">04</span>Web App Overview</a>
    <div class="nav-section-label">Operations</div>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch5" onclick="showPage('ch5',this)"><span class="num">05</span>Home Dashboard</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch6" onclick="showPage('ch6',this)"><span class="num">06</span>Assets</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch7" onclick="showPage('ch7',this)"><span class="num">07</span>Trips</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch8" onclick="showPage('ch8',this)"><span class="num">08</span>Sessions</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch9" onclick="showPage('ch9',this)"><span class="num">09</span>Rentals</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch10" onclick="showPage('ch10',this)"><span class="num">10</span>Hub Energy</a>
    <div class="nav-section-label">Assets &amp; People</div>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch11" onclick="showPage('ch11',this)"><span class="num">11</span>Batteries</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch12" onclick="showPage('ch12',this)"><span class="num">12</span>Chargers</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch13" onclick="showPage('ch13',this)"><span class="num">13</span>Users</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch14" onclick="showPage('ch14',this)"><span class="num">14</span>Requests</a>
    <div class="nav-section-label">Configuration</div>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch15" onclick="showPage('ch15',this)"><span class="num">15</span>Locations</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch16" onclick="showPage('ch16',this)"><span class="num">16</span>Containers</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch17" onclick="showPage('ch17',this)"><span class="num">17</span>Service</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch18" onclick="showPage('ch18',this)"><span class="num">18</span>Rates Manager</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch19" onclick="showPage('ch19',this)"><span class="num">19</span>Revenue Manager</a>
    <a class="nav-item" data-page="ch20" onclick="showPage('ch20',this)"><span class="num">20</span>Settings</a>
  </div>
</nav>
<div id="main">
  <div id="topbar">
    <div id="topbar-search">
      <span class="topbar-search-icon">⌕</span>
      <input type="text" id="searchInput" placeholder="Search documentation… (Ctrl+K)" autocomplete="off"/>
      <div id="search-results"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="topbar-right">
      <span class="topbar-badge">April 2026</span>
      <span style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:12px;color:var(--text-light)">Antarctica Global</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="content">
<!-- HOME PAGE -->
<div class="chapter-page active" id="page-home">
  <div class="chapter-hero">
    <div class="chapter-tag">Documentation</div>
    <h1>Songa Mobility Platform</h1>
    <p class="lead">Complete reference documentation for the Songa web application — all modules, entities, and operational flows. Prepared by Antarctica Global Technology and Consulting, April 2026.</p>
  </div>
  <p style="font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:14px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-bottom:20px">20 chapters · Use the search bar above or navigate by section below</p>
  <div class="home-grid">
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch1',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 01</div><div class="home-card-title">Introduction</div><div class="home-card-desc">About Songa, Antarctica Global, and platform philosophy</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch2',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 02</div><div class="home-card-title">Platform Architecture</div><div class="home-card-desc">Tech stack, multi-tenancy, IoT hardware, third-party integrations</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch3',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 03</div><div class="home-card-title">Core Entities</div><div class="home-card-desc">Hubs, trikes, batteries, drivers, farmers, trips, sessions</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch4',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 04</div><div class="home-card-title">Web App Overview</div><div class="home-card-desc">Navigation structure, authentication, onboarding</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch5',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 05</div><div class="home-card-title">Home Dashboard</div><div class="home-card-desc">KPI cards, interactive map, trike quick list</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch6',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 06</div><div class="home-card-title">Assets</div><div class="home-card-desc">Vehicles (trikes) and agri-tech equipment management</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch7',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 07</div><div class="home-card-title">Trips</div><div class="home-card-desc">Creating trips, stops, route optimisation, receipt verification</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch8',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 08</div><div class="home-card-title">Sessions</div><div class="home-card-desc">Agri-tech service operations, USSD flow, session creation</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch9',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 09</div><div class="home-card-title">Rentals</div><div class="home-card-desc">Trike rental management, fees, approval flow</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch10',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 10</div><div class="home-card-title">Hub Energy</div><div class="home-card-desc">Real-time energy monitoring, supply control panel</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch11',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 11</div><div class="home-card-title">Batteries</div><div class="home-card-desc">Battery management, IoT telemetry, inter-hub transfers</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch12',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 12</div><div class="home-card-title">Chargers</div><div class="home-card-desc">Smart charger infrastructure, IoT nodes, BMS data</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch13',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 13</div><div class="home-card-title">Users</div><div class="home-card-desc">Drivers, partners, calendar, time-off, ratings</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch14',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 14</div><div class="home-card-title">Requests</div><div class="home-card-desc">USSD inbox, transport/session/purchase requests, rentals</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch15',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 15</div><div class="home-card-title">Locations</div><div class="home-card-desc">Hub stations, collection points, delivery points</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch16',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 16</div><div class="home-card-title">Containers</div><div class="home-card-desc">Canisters and crates, QR codes, trip traceability</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch17',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 17</div><div class="home-card-title">Service</div><div class="home-card-desc">Asset maintenance, ERP integration, repair completion</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch18',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 18</div><div class="home-card-title">Rates Manager</div><div class="home-card-desc">Commodity, energy, and agri-tech commission rates</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch19',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 19</div><div class="home-card-title">Revenue Manager</div><div class="home-card-desc">Farmer payments, driver commission, off-taker collections</div></a>
    <a class="home-card" onclick="showPage('ch20',null)"><div class="home-card-num">Chapter 20</div><div class="home-card-title">Settings</div><div class="home-card-desc">Account management, system users, roles</div></a>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- CH1 -->
<div class="chapter-page" id="page-ch1">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a onclick="showPage('home',null)">Home</a> › Chapter 1</div>
  <div class="chapter-hero"><div class="chapter-tag">Chapter 01</div><h1>Introduction</h1><p class="lead">About this document, Songa Mobility, Antarctica Global, and the three principles that underpin the platform.</p></div>
  <div class="doc-body">
    <h2 class="section-h2">1.1 About This Document</h2>
    <p>This is a working reference document describing the Songa Mobility Web Application as built and maintained by Antarctica Global Technology and Consulting. It covers modules and flows documented to date — additional sections are being added as documentation progresses. Content reflects the platform as it currently stands, not as it is planned.</p>
    <p>Intended audience: product managers, engineers, implementation partners, and operational stakeholders who need to understand how each module, entity, and flow works across the Songa web application.</p>
    <h2 class="section-h2">1.2 About Songa Mobility</h2>
    <p>Songa Mobility (<code>songa.mobi</code>) is a hub-based clean energy and mobility ecosystem operating in the Kisii region of Kenya. Songa operates a fleet of electric cargo trikes that serve smallholder farmers across the region, collecting agricultural produce — primarily milk — and delivering it to offtakers (dairies and produce buyers).</p>
    <p>In addition to its transport and aggregation operations, Songa provides Power Africa agri-tech services through motorised equipment deployed at farms, including tillers, millers, threshers, grinders, chaff cutters, and water pumps.</p>
    <div class="info-box"><strong>Revenue model:</strong> All batteries are owned by Songa. Battery energy is the primary revenue stream — drivers are charged for the energy consumed during every trip, session, and rental. All assets operate out of hub stations distributed across the Kisii region.</div>
    <h2 class="section-h2">1.3 About Antarctica Global</h2>
    <p>Antarctica Global Technology and Consulting is a climate technology company headquartered in Mumbai, with offices in Paris and Nairobi. Antarctica serves as the exclusive technology partner for Songa Mobility, responsible for full software development, IoT integration, and platform architecture — including the Web Application, Mobile Application, IoT data pipeline, and all third-party integrations.</p>
    <h2 class="section-h2">1.4 Platform Philosophy</h2>
    <div class="step-list">
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Every operational event generates structured financial data.</strong> A trip completed, a battery charged, a session conducted — all flow downstream into financial calculations.</div></div>
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Physical assets are IoT-connected wherever possible.</strong> Trikes, batteries, chargers, and hub inverters make the web platform a live mirror of ground reality rather than a manual record.</div></div>
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Multi-tenant SaaS architecture.</strong> The platform allows Songa to onboard additional clients with their own isolated configurations, roles, and module sets.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- CH2 -->
<div class="chapter-page" id="page-ch2">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a onclick="showPage('home',null)">Home</a> › Chapter 2</div>
  <div class="chapter-hero"><div class="chapter-tag">Chapter 02</div><h1>Platform Architecture</h1><p class="lead">Technical stack, multi-tenancy model, IoT hardware integrations, and third-party services. Deployed on AWS Paris (eu-west-3).</p></div>
  <div class="doc-body">
    <h2 class="section-h2">2.1 High-Level Architecture</h2>
    <div class="arch-diagram">
      <div class="arch-row">
        <div class="arch-box teal"><div class="ab-label">Frontend</div><div class="ab-val">ReactJS on Vercel</div><div class="ab-sub">fleet.songa.mobi</div></div>
        <div class="arch-box teal"><div class="ab-label">Backend API</div><div class="ab-val">Node.js 18 / Express</div><div class="ab-sub">AWS EC2 · 3 Docker containers · Nginx</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-row">
        <div class="arch-box navy"><div class="ab-label">Database</div><div class="ab-val">PostgreSQL 14.10</div><div class="ab-sub">AWS RDS Paris · Liquibase</div></div>
        <div class="arch-box navy"><div class="ab-label">IoT Platform</div><div class="ab-val">Thingsboard</div><div class="ab-sub">AWS EC2 · TCU + HCU bridge</div></div>
        <div class="arch-box"><div class="ab-label">Storage / Email</div><div class="ab-val">AWS S3 + SES</div><div class="ab-sub">Receipts, licences, transactional email</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Technology</th><th>Details</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Frontend</td><td>ReactJS on Vercel</td><td>Production: <code>fleet.songa.mobi</code> · Staging: <code>fleet.staging.songa.mobi</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Backend API</td><td>Node.js 18 LTS + Express</td><td>Single EC2, Elastic IP, ports 4000/4001/4002, TLS via Certbot</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Database</td><td>PostgreSQL 14.10 on RDS</td><td>3 schemas: production, staging, dev. Version control via Liquibase</td></tr>
      <tr><td>IoT Platform</td><td>Thingsboard</td><td>Dedicated EC2, time-series DB + message queue. Bridges TCU and HCU data.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Secrets</td><td>Doppler</td><td>Workspace: EASVRM · Project: songa-mobility-platform</td></tr>
      <tr><td>CI/CD</td><td>Vercel + Bitbucket Pipeline</td><td>Branch strategy: local → develop → staging → production</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h2 class="section-h2">2.2 Multi-Tenancy</h2>
    <p>The platform is architected as a multi-tenant SaaS system. Songa itself is Tenant 1. Additional clients can be onboarded as separate tenants, each with their own configuration of modules, roles, permissions, and notification rules — all within a single shared database with schema-level isolation. Songa owns all data.</p>
    <h2 class="section-h2">2.3 Access Control</h2>
    <p>Three-tier ACL system. At the top level, the Admin Panel controls what modules and roles are available to each tenant. Within each tenant, the Super Admin creates users and assigns roles.</p>
    <div class="pill-wrap"><span class="badge badge-teal">Super Admin</span><span class="badge badge-blue">Hub Manager</span><span class="badge badge-gray">Fleet Manager / Operator</span><span class="badge badge-gray">Driver (mobile only)</span></div>
    <h2 class="section-h2">2.4 IoT Hardware Integrations</h2>
    <h3 class="section-h3">TCU — Trike Control Unit</h3>
    <p>The onboard smart computer installed on each trike. Communicates with batteries via RS485 and transmits real-time GPS (approx. every 10–12 seconds), battery BMS data (SOC, voltage, current, temperature), and vehicle metrics (speed, mileage) to the IoT platform. TCU integration: ongoing.</p>
    <h3 class="section-h3">HCU — Hub Control Unit</h3>
    <p>Manages solar energy at hub stations. Connects to the inverter and smart chargers, transmitting energy production, storage, and consumption data. Smart chargers connected to the HCU are dual-purpose: they charge batteries and simultaneously provide live BMS data. HCU integration: in progress.</p>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Smart Chargers</h3>
    <p>Registered on the platform with an IoT Device ID linking each physical charger to its Thingsboard node profile. Batteries are identified via their BMS ID. All charger state changes on the IoT platform are reflected on Songa in real time.</p>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Auto Switcher</h3>
    <p>Automatically switches the GPS source for each trike between TCU-based IoT GPS and driver mobile GPS based on signal strength and satellite count. Built on top of the manual toggle per trike row.</p>
    <h2 class="section-h2">2.5 Third-Party Integrations</h2>
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Integration</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
      <tr><td>ERP System (ERPNext)</td><td>Financial system of record. Receives farmer payment data, driver commissions, maintenance entries. Sends confirmations back via the Songa Controller Layer middleware.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Google Maps</td><td>Navigation used by drivers on the Mobile App for point-to-point routing.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Thingsboard</td><td>IoT data broker receiving real-time telemetry from TCUs (trikes) and HCUs (hubs).</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Africa's Talking</td><td>Powers the USSD service (<code>*384*385#</code>) and two-way SMS for farmers and drivers.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Weather API</td><td>Provides temperature and sunset time on Hub Energy Management and main dashboards.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>AWS SES</td><td>Transactional email for user invitations, OTPs, and platform notifications.</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- CH3 -->
<div class="chapter-page" id="page-ch3">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a onclick="showPage('home',null)">Home</a> › Chapter 3</div>
  <div class="chapter-hero"><div class="chapter-tag">Chapter 03</div><h1>Core Entities</h1><p class="lead">Every operational flow involves interactions between these entities. Understanding them is a prerequisite to understanding modules and flows.</p></div>
  <div class="doc-body">
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Entity</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Hubs</td><td>Physical centres of operations. Every asset is assigned to a hub as its permanent home. Trips start and end at hubs. Hub-level energy management is tracked through the Hub Energy Management module.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Trikes</td><td>Electric cargo three-wheelers — the primary transport asset. Assigned to hubs, associated with batteries, linked to drivers on trips or rentals. Where a TCU is installed, trikes transmit real-time GPS and battery data. Remote mobilisation/immobilisation available via IoT.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Batteries</td><td>Smart battery packs owned entirely by Songa. The primary revenue-generating asset — every trip, session, and rental generates an energy charge based on kWh consumed. Communicate with TCUs when on trikes and with smart chargers when charging.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Chargers</td><td>IoT-connected charging units at hub stations. Two types: Canbus (full two-way BMS communication) and Non-Canbus (charging only, limited data). Charger status reflects on Songa in real time.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drivers</td><td>Registered system users with access to the Songa Mobile App. Conduct aggregation trips, operate agri-tech assets in sessions, and can rent trikes. Earn commission based on weight collected; charged for energy consumed during every operation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Farmers</td><td>Registered smallholder agricultural producers. Act as collection points on aggregation trips and as requesters of agri-tech sessions via USSD. Each has a QR code for field identification.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Offtakers</td><td>Buyers of agricultural produce (dairies, processing facilities). Drivers deliver collected milk and must upload a receipt ID and photo as proof before a trip can be completed.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Trips</td><td>Structured, multi-stop operational journeys. Always begin and end at the hub parking lot. Must have delivery receipts verified by a Hub Manager before financial data flows downstream.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Sessions</td><td>Single-farmer, single-asset agri-tech service operations. Conducted by an agent at a farm location; concluded with actual vs. estimated comparison, M-Pesa reference, and optional feedback.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Rentals</td><td>Allow registered Songa drivers to rent a trike for independent use. External individuals not permitted. Fees comprise a standard daily rate plus energy consumption charges.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Agri-Tech Assets</td><td>Power Africa motorised equipment: Tillers, Millers, Grinders, Threshers, Chaff Cutters, Water Pumps, Ploughs. Assigned to hubs, associated with batteries, deployed in sessions.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Canisters &amp; Crates</td><td>Physical containers for transporting produce. Registered as assets, assigned to hubs, associated with trips. QR-coded for per-canister, per-farmer traceability.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Locations</td><td>Named geographic points — hub stations, farm collection points, delivery points, parking lots. Defined by name, address, and GPS coordinates. All other entities nest under hub locations. Foundational to the entire platform.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Partners</td><td>Umbrella term for Farmers and Offtakers. Partners have QR codes and M-Pesa numbers for payments.</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- CH4 -->
<div class="chapter-page" id="page-ch4">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a onclick="showPage('home',null)">Home</a> › Chapter 4</div>
  <div class="chapter-hero"><div class="chapter-tag">Chapter 04</div><h1>Web Application Overview</h1><p class="lead">Navigation structure, authentication, and onboarding for the Songa web application at fleet.songa.mobi.</p></div>
  <div class="doc-body">
    <h2 class="section-h2">4.1 Navigation Structure</h2>
    <p>The web application is accessible at <code>fleet.songa.mobi</code> — a single-page React application with a persistent left navigation sidebar. The top bar displays the current date, weather (temperature and location), and a notification bell.</p>
    <p>Full set of navigation modules (visibility governed by tenant configuration):</p>
    <div class="pill-wrap"><span class="pill">Home</span><span class="pill">Assets</span><span class="pill">Trips</span><span class="pill">Sessions</span><span class="pill">Rentals</span><span class="pill">Hubs</span><span class="pill">Batteries</span><span class="pill">Chargers</span><span class="pill">Users</span><span class="pill">Requests</span><span class="pill">Locations</span><span class="pill">QR Codes</span><span class="pill">Services</span><span class="pill">Revenue Manager</span><span class="pill">Rates Manager</span><span class="pill">Settings</span></div>
    <h2 class="section-h2">4.2 Authentication and Onboarding</h2>
    <p>Users are invited to the platform via email by an administrator. The invitation contains a one-time password (OTP) which forms part of two-factor authentication. Upon accepting, new users complete an onboarding wizard collecting organisation name, number of vehicles, drivers, hubs, and organisation location.</p>
    <div class="info-box"><strong>Invite-only:</strong> There is no open sign-up flow. Without an invitation, no one can enter the Songa ecosystem. The traditional username/password requirement is eliminated — OTP-based flow is the sole entry point.</div>
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Actor</th><th>Flow</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Web users</td><td>Admin invites via email → OTP received → onboarding wizard → platform access</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drivers</td><td>Added in system → invitation email → redirect to mobile app → sign up and enter ecosystem</td></tr>
      <tr><td>New tenants</td><td>Invited from Admin Panel → OTP signup → tenant configuration</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- CH5 -->
<div class="chapter-page" id="page-ch5">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a onclick="showPage('home',null)">Home</a> › Chapter 5</div>
  <div class="chapter-hero"><div class="chapter-tag">Chapter 05</div><h1>Home Dashboard</h1><p class="lead">The operational command centre of the platform — a unified real-time view of the entire Songa operation across all hubs and assets.</p></div>
  <div class="doc-body">
    <h2 class="section-h2">5.1 KPI Cards</h2>
    <p>Six summary cards displayed across the top of the home page. Each card is clickable and links to its respective module:</p>
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Card</th><th>What It Shows</th></tr>
      <tr><td>All Assets</td><td>Total count of all assets registered in the system (trikes + agri-tech equipment combined)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>All Trips</td><td>Cumulative count of all trips created on the platform</td></tr>
      <tr><td>All Sessions</td><td>Cumulative count of all sessions created</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Total Milk Delivered</td><td>Aggregate litres of milk delivered across all completed trips — headline operational impact metric</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Batteries</td><td>Count of batteries currently at hub stations, in trikes, and in service</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Drivers / Partners</td><td>Total registered drivers and partners in the system</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h2 class="section-h2">5.2 Interactive Map</h2>
    <p>The right side of the home page shows a full-panel interactive map with real-time asset locations. Asset positions are dynamic:</p>
    <ul class="doc-ul"><li>Where a <strong>TCU is active</strong>, the map pin updates in real time as the trike moves</li><li>Where the TCU is unavailable, the <strong>driver's mobile GPS</strong> serves as the location source</li><li>When a trike is not on a trip, location defaults to the <strong>Hub Station</strong></li></ul>
    <p>Quick-filter buttons below the KPI cards toggle visibility of Hub Stations, Farms, and Trikes. Clicking an asset pin shows a tooltip with: asset ID, status, associated driver, location name, speed, payload, and battery percentage — plus a direct link to the asset's detail page.</p>
    <h2 class="section-h2">5.3 Trike Quick List</h2>
    <p>The left panel contains a searchable list of all registered trikes. Searching by registration number or driver name selects the corresponding map pin and centres the view on its current location — allowing hub managers to instantly locate any trike without navigating away.</p>
    <h2 class="section-h2">5.4 Quick Navigation</h2>
    <p>Every KPI card, map pin, and trike list entry acts as a direct shortcut. KPI cards link to module listings, asset pins link to asset detail pages, and trike entries link to trike detail views in the Assets module.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- CH6 -->
<div class="chapter-page" id="page-ch6">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a onclick="showPage('home',null)">Home</a> › Chapter 6</div>
  <div class="chapter-hero"><div class="chapter-tag">Chapter 06</div><h1>Assets</h1><p class="lead">The Assets module consolidates Vehicles (Trikes) and Agri-Tech equipment under a single navigation item, accessible via two tabs.</p></div>
  <div class="doc-body">
    <h2 class="section-h2">6.1 Vehicles (Trikes)</h2>

<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page012_img026.jpeg" alt="Assets — Vehicles (Trikes) listing with status badges and IoT controls" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Assets — Vehicles (Trikes) listing with status badges and IoT controls</figcaption>
</figure>

    <h3 class="section-h3">Trike Statuses</h3>
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-green">On Trip</span></td><td>Currently on an active aggregation trip with an associated driver</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-amber">Dispatched</span></td><td>Dispatched for a rental; driver associated and rental is active</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-blue">Hub Station</span></td><td>At its assigned hub station and available for dispatch</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-red">Out of Geofence</span></td><td>Moved outside configured geofence boundary; notification triggered immediately</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-gray">Service</span></td><td>Currently undergoing maintenance; not available for operations</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h3 class="section-h3">IoT Controls</h3>
    <div class="field-list">
      <div class="field-item"><div class="field-name">Mobilise / Immobilise</div><div class="field-desc">Remotely controls the trike's ability to operate via the TCU. Immobilise cuts the trike's electrical connection to its battery instantly — no delay between web action and hardware response. Button label and colour reflect current hardware state.</div></div>
      <div class="field-item"><div class="field-name">GPS Source Toggle</div><div class="field-desc">Switches location tracking between TCU-based IoT GPS and driver mobile phone GPS, per trike, in real time. The Auto Switcher automates this based on signal strength, but the manual toggle remains for override.</div></div>
    </div>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Three-Dot Actions per Trike Row</h3>
    <p>View Details · Edit Details · Add Issues · View Issues · View QR Code · Add to Service · Retire · Delete Trike</p>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Trike Detail Page</h3>
    <p>Split between a left panel (operational data) and a right panel (live map). Left panel shows live IoT metrics: Current Speed, Average Speed, Distance Covered, Mileage, and Load Utilisation (kg/km ratio — a measure of operational efficiency). A Battery Pack section visualises each battery slot (B1, B2…) as a bar indicator showing charge percentage. Below: full trip history table.</p>
    <p>The right panel shows the trike's live location with a Geofence button — hub managers can draw a custom boundary. If the trike exits, status updates to Out of Geofence and notifications are triggered.</p>

<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page014_img031.jpeg" alt="Trike detail — live IoT metrics, battery pack slots, trip history, and live map with Geofence" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Trike detail — live IoT metrics, battery pack slots, trip history, and live map with Geofence</figcaption>
</figure>

    <h3 class="section-h3">Add Trike — Form Fields</h3>
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Trike Registration Number</td><td>Official vehicle registration (e.g. KTWD318K)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Insurance Validity</td><td>Date picker for insurance expiry</td></tr>
      <tr><td>IoT Device ID</td><td>TCU device ID on the IoT platform — required for live data linkage</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Owned?</td><td>Toggle: Songa-owned vs. lease arrangement. Affects rental fee calculation.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Total Capacity</td><td>Max payload in kg. Used in load utilisation calculations and speed limiter thresholds.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hub Station</td><td>Permanent home hub assignment</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Safety Checklist Configuration</h3>
    <p>Hub managers configure a global safety checklist that drivers must complete before every trip and rental. Each item is framed as a question specific to a trike part (e.g. "Are the brakes functional?"). Items can be flagged as mandatory.</p>
    <div class="warn-box">If a driver fails a mandatory checklist item, the screen displays <strong>"TRIKE IS NOT SAFE TO DRIVE"</strong> and prevents proceeding. The driver can inform the Fleet Manager (automated email) or scan an alternative trike.</div>
    <h2 class="section-h2">6.2 Agri-Tech Assets</h2>

<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page016_img037.jpeg" alt="Assets — Agri-Tech tab with asset type colour-coded badges and per-type safety checklist" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Assets — Agri-Tech tab with asset type colour-coded badges and per-type safety checklist</figcaption>
</figure>

    <p>Supported asset types: <strong>Tiller</strong> · <strong>Miller</strong> · <strong>Grinder</strong> · <strong>Thresher</strong> · <strong>Chaff Cutter</strong> · <strong>Water Pump</strong> · <strong>Plough</strong> — each with a distinct colour-coded badge.</p>
    <p>Statuses: <span class="badge badge-green">In Session</span> · <span class="badge badge-blue">Hub Station</span> · <span class="badge badge-gray">Service</span></p>

<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page017_img040.jpeg" alt="Agri-Tech detail — asset overview, battery pack slots, session history, and live location map" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Agri-Tech detail — asset overview, battery pack slots, session history, and live location map</figcaption>
</figure>

    <p>Each asset type has its own safety checklist, configured independently from the trike checklist via the Checklist dropdown on the Agri-Tech tab. Agri-tech assets are not individually TCU-connected — no IoT Device ID required.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<!-- CH7 -->
<div class="chapter-page" id="page-ch7">
  <div class="breadcrumb"><a onclick="showPage('home',null)">Home</a> › Chapter 7</div>
  <div class="chapter-hero"><div class="chapter-tag">Chapter 07</div><h1>Trips</h1><p class="lead">The operational backbone of Songa's dairy aggregation model. Trips are structured, multi-stop journeys that always originate and terminate at the hub's parking lot.</p></div>
  <div class="doc-body">

<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page018_img043.jpeg" alt="Trips listing — status badges, filter controls, and trip summary rows" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Trips listing — status badges, filter controls, and trip summary rows</figcaption>
</figure>

    <h2 class="section-h2">7.1 Trip Statuses</h2>
    <table class="doc-table">
      <tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-blue">Upcoming</span></td><td>Scheduled for a future date/time. Not yet started by the driver.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-green">Ongoing</span></td><td>Currently being executed by the driver on the Mobile App.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-gray">Completed</span></td><td>Executed and all delivery receipts verified. Financial data has flowed downstream — farmer payments calculated, driver commission logged.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><span class="badge badge-amber">Completed ⚠</span></td><td>Physically executed but one or more delivery receipts not yet verified. Farmer payments and driver commission on hold until verification is complete.</td></tr>
    </table>

<figure class="doc-screenshot doc-screenshot-wide">
  <img src="img/page019_img046.png" alt="Trip detail page — KPI cards, stop timeline, and receipt verification" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Trip detail page — KPI cards, stop timeline, and receipt verification</figcaption>
</figure>

    <h2 class="section-h2">7.2 Trip Detail Page</h2>
    <p>Overview KPI cards: Number of Stops · Total Distance (km) · Trip Duration · Total Weight Collected (kg) · Total Weight Delivered (kg) · Total Spoilt Milk (kg). These update dynamically as the trip progresses.</p>
    <p>Trip Info section: Driver Name, Trike Number, Date, Batteries Assigned, Odometer Start-End, Payload, Safety Checklist score (clickable to view all responses), and a Speed Limit info button showing the limit applied based on payload weight.</p>
    <p>Stops displayed as a visual timeline — Stop 1 tagged Origin, final stop tagged Destination, intermediate stops numbered with location names. Each stop shows the farmers from whom milk was collected, quantities, canisters used, and the POC at the delivery point.</p>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Receipt Verification</h3>
    <p>Drivers upload a receipt ID and photo when delivering to an offtaker. The web interface shows a Verification Pending label for unverified deliveries. The Hub Manager reviews and confirms on the trip detail page.</p>
    <div class="info-box"><strong>Financial gate:</strong> Financial data (farmer payments, driver commission) does not flow until the physical evidence of delivery has been confirmed by the Hub Manager. A trip with unverified receipts shows <span class="badge badge-amber">Completed ⚠</span> — not the clean Completed state.</div>
    <h2 class="section-h2">7.3 Creating a Trip — 5-Step Wizard</h2>

<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page021_img051.jpeg" alt="Create Trip — Step 1: stop selection with drag-to-reorder and Optimise Route" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Create Trip — Step 1: stop selection with drag-to-reorder and Optimise Route</figcaption>
</figure>


<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page022_img054.jpeg" alt="Create Trip — Step 2: schedule and route optimisation applied" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Create Trip — Step 2: schedule and route optimisation applied</figcaption>
</figure>


<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page023_img057.jpeg" alt="Create Trip — Step 3: recurrence configuration with day-of-week selector" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Create Trip — Step 3: recurrence configuration with day-of-week selector</figcaption>
</figure>


<figure class="doc-screenshot">
  <img src="img/page024_img060.jpeg" alt="Create Trip — Step 5: battery selection with Recommended Number of Batteries system banner" loading="lazy">
  <figcaption>Create Trip — Step 5: battery selection with Recommended Number of Batteries system banner</figcaption>
</figure>

    <div class="step-list">
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Select Stops</strong> — Build the trip route. Origin and Destination (hub parking lot) are fixed. Add intermediate stops with Location, Activity (Collection or Delivery), and Commodity. Drag-to-reorder. Use Optimise Route to apply the proprietary route algorithm.</div></div>
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Schedule Trip</strong> — Trip Date and Time Slot. Optional: enable Set Recurrence with day-of-week selector (S M T W T F S) and end date to auto-generate recurring trips — eliminating the need to manually create the same route daily.</div></div>
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Select Driver</strong> — Searchable list of available drivers. Drivers on approved leave, currently suspended, or already assigned to a trip on the same date are not shown.</div></div>
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">4</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Select Trike (Optional)</strong> — Available trikes at the hub's parking lot with battery level indicators. Trike selection is optional at creation.</div></div>
      <div class="step-item"><div class="step-num">5</div><div class="step-body"><strong>Select Batteries (Optional)</strong> — System shows a Recommended Number of Batteries banner (derived from trip distance, estimated weight, and historical energy consumption data). A trip cannot be conducted unless a trike and batteries are associated; Hub Managers receive reminders if assignment is pending.</div></div>
    </div>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Route Validation Rules</h3>
    <div class="field-list">
      <div class="field-item"><div class="field-name">Rule 1</div><div class="field-desc">The first stop after origin cannot be a delivery point</div></div>
      <div class="field-item"><div class="field-name">Rule 2</div><div class="field-desc">The last stop before destination cannot be a collection point</div></div>
      <div class="field-item"><div class="field-name">Rule 3</div><div class="field-desc">Collection of a given commodity must always precede its delivery</div></div>
      <div class="field-item"><div class="field-name">Rule 4</div><div class="field-desc">A single stop cannot have both collection and delivery of the same commodity</div></div>
      <div class="field-item"><div class="field-name">Rule 5</div><div class="field-desc">Duplicate stops with the same activity are prevented</div></div>
    </div>
    <h3 class="section-h3">Route Optimisation Algorithm</h3>
    <p>Rather than evaluating all possible stop orderings (n! permutations), the algorithm first eliminates invalid sequences by enforcing the collection-before-delivery constraint and first/last stop rules. From the remaining valid sequences, it calculates total GPS-coordinate-based distance for each and selects the route with the lowest total distance — including source and destination in that calculation. Designed by Antarctica specifically for the constraints of the Songa operation.</p>
  </div>
</div>
